陳宏傑的個人資料 - 國立暨南國際大學 外國語文學系

















您的瀏覽器不支援Javascript，部分功能將無法呈現。


“It will never rain roses, when we want to have more roses we must plant trees. ” - G. Eliot “Do not for one repulse, for go the purpose that you resolved to effort. ”  - William  Shakespeare“If you doubt yourself, then indeed you stand on shaky ground. ” - Ibsen “When all else is lost, the future still remains.”- Bovee“We have two ears and only one tongue in order that we may hear more and speak less.”- Pope“True merit is like a river, the deeper it is the less noise it makes.”- Edward F Halifax“Often the test of courage is not to die but to live.”- Alfieri“The important thing in life is to have a great aim, and the determination to attain it.”- Johan Wolfgang von Goethe“The man with a new idea is a crank until the idea succeeds.”- Mark Twain“If you would go up high, then use your own legs! Do not let yourselves carried aloft; do not seat yourselves on other people's backs and heads.”- F.W. Nietzsche“Living without an aim is like sailing without a compass.”- Davy de La Pailleterie“Truth needs no colour; beauty, no pencil.”- William Shakespeare“A man should never be ashamed to own that he has been in the wrong, which is but saying, in other words, that he is wiser today than he was yesterday.”- Alexander Pope“Freedom is not worth having if it does not connote freedom to err.”- Mahatma Gandhi“No man is rich enough to buy back his past.”- Oscar Wilde“Beauty is how you feel inside, and it reflects in your eyes. It is not something physical.”- Bernard Cornfeld“Luck affects everything. Let your hook always be cast in the stream where you least expect there will be a fish.”- Ovid“To conquer fear is the brginning of wisdom.” - Bertrand Russell“Those who do not feel pain seldom think that is is felt.”- Sammuel Johnson“Then come kiss me, sweet and twenty, youth's a stuff will not endure. ” -William Shakespeare“What's in a name? That which we call a rose by any other name would smell as sweet.”- William Shakespeare“Virtue is bold, and goodness never fearful.”- William Shakespeare“The quality of mercy is not strain’d. It droppeth as the gentle rain from heaven upon the place beneath. It is twice blest: It blesseth him that gives and him that takes.” - Merchant of Venice






